======================================================================
1) Affected Software

* libsndfile version 1.0.28. Other versions may also be affected.

======================================================================
2) Severity

Rating: Moderately critical
Impact: Exposure of sensitive information
Where:  From remote

======================================================================
3) Description of Vulnerability

Secunia Research has discovered a vulnerability in libsndfile, which
can be exploited by malicious people to disclose potentially sensitive
information.

The vulnerability is caused due to an error in the
"aiff_read_chanmap()" function (src/aiff.c), which can be exploited to
cause an out-of-bounds read memory access via a specially crafted AIFF
file.

The vulnerability is confirmed in version 1.0.28. Other versions may
also be affected.

======================================================================
4) Solution

Fixed in the source code repository.
https://github.com/erikd/libsndfile/commit/f833c53cb596e9e1792949f762e0b33661822748

======================================================================
5) Time Table

2017/05/23 - Maintainer contacted with the vulnerability details.
2017/05/23 - Maintainer confirmed the vulnerability.
2017/05/24 - Maintainer released a fix.
2017/06/12 - Release of Secunia Advisory SA76717.
2017/06/12 - Public disclosure of Secunia Research Advisory.

======================================================================
6) Credits

Discovered by Laurent Delosieres, Secunia Research at Flexera Software

